      • moveDocument

        public void moveDocument(String fromFolder,
                         String toFolder)
                  throws IOException
        This method will move a document (a Snippet db record) from the fromFolder to the toFolder. Both parameters are optional. If no fromFolder parameter is designated, the document will be moved to the toFolder but will not be removed from any other folder. If no toFolder parameter is designated, the document will be removed from the fromFolder but it will not be placed into any other folder.
        Parameters:
        fromFolder - folder from which entries will be removed
        toFolder - folder to which entries will be added
        Throws:
        IOException - exception occurred

      • moveDocumentByType

        public void moveDocumentByType(String fromFolder,
                               String toFolder,
                               String type)
        This method will copy all documents (Snippet db records) that match the docyType of this document from this document's home folder to the toFolder. Both fromFolder and toFolder parameters are optional. If no fromFolder parameter is designated, the documents will be moved to the toFolder but will not be removed from any other folder. If no toFolder parameter is designated, the documents will be removed from the fromFolder but will not be placed into any other folder.
        Parameters:
        fromFolder - folder from which entries will be removed
        toFolder - folder to which entries will be added
        type - docType to move

      • updateModified

        public void updateModified()
        This method sets the modified column of the current db record to the current date/time. We are sorting on modified instead of updated because we want to sort only on major status jumps and this method allows us to assure that modified is only updated when we want it to be updated.

      • updateStackProgress

        public void updateStackProgress(String isComplete)
        In order to assure that all documents in a stack move forward together (the Index/Process/Review button is correct for the current state of the stack), the Master Stack document will hold the current status of all Charge/Payment documents in the stack. This method updates that status for the current document.

      • wpostDocuSign

        public String wpostDocuSign(String url,
                            org.mozilla.javascript.NativeArray parms,
                            org.mozilla.javascript.NativeArray headers)
        Send a multipart/form POST request to Docusign. This method is needed because the geniuses at DocuSign don't seem to support reall multipart/form POST requests. It looks like they don't expect any names on the parameters but instead just support two parameters: the JSON signature request information and the uploaded file. Since they don't support names for the parameters, we can't use the standard HTTP client libraries because they always send name/value pairs. The file to POST will be pulled from the URL of the current Snippet. Warning, this method assumes that any response will be text (is turned into a String).
        Parameters:
        url - URL to post to
        parms - extra parameters to post
        headers - extra headers to post
        Returns:
        response body that was received.
